The paper deals with detecting anomalous faces using unsupervised methods and constructing a feature vector. This involves image processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of autoencoders and proposes a new method, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the need for accurate detection of rare anomalies, which is related to the field of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses a dataset of celebrity images, which is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
